snippet.textDisplay:
Why has this been turned into a music video? It's an old track for one. Coke Studio has never been about making music videos. To me it's about making a fusion song in a studio (hence Coke STUDIO) where we can see all the singers including the musicians performing together on one stage.

As for this track, I've never really liked Hard Kaur and her lyrics are nowhere near scorching like you describe. "Better than the rest", she most definately isn't, not sure why she considers herself to be "Hip Hop's monolith" either. It would've been better to just have Bhanvari Devi by herself on this one, in my opinion.
